lead_paragraph: Lower-league footballers can take inspiration from players like Leicester City forward Jamie Vardy, who plied his trade in various tiers of the game prior to his England call-up for Euro 2016, Northern Ireland striker Conor Washington has said.

headline.print_headline: Vardy an Inspiration for Lower-League Players-Washington
